# Class Member Claim Form

Provides a standardized claim form template and guidance to aid class members in submitting settlement claims accurately and complying with legal and administrative requirements.

## Prerequisites

1. Settlement agreement and preliminary or final approval order  
2. Court details: caption, case number, judge, venue  
3. Class definition and class period  
4. Claim categories, eligibility criteria, and payment formulas  
5. Claim submission deadline, applicable time zone, postmark vs received rule, and submission methods  
6. Settlement administrator contact information and portal URLs  
7. Required documentation and any eligibility thresholds waiving documentation  
8. Privacy notice, data retention, and E-SIGN policy compliance  
9. Accessibility and language translation requirements

## Output Structure / Process

### Section Checklist

| Section                 | Must Include                          | Notes                                               |
|-------------------------|-------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Case Information        | Caption, case number, court name    | Match official court documents                      |
| Claimant Information     | Full name, contact, representative  | Include guardian info if claimant is minor          |
| Class Criteria          | Eligibility requirements             | Reference class definition                           |
| Claim Categories         | Detailed claim options               | Include payment categories and formulas             |
| Documentation           | Required supporting documents        | Specify when documentation is waived                 |
| Certification & Release | Certifications, signature lines     | Include perjury warnings and applicable waivers [VERIFY] |
| Submission Instructions | Deadlines, methods, addresses        | Specify time zone and postmark vs received rule     |
| Administrator Use       | Internal tracking fields             | Optional, for settlement admin use only              |

### Field Rules

| Field                  | Required? | Format / Validation                          |
|------------------------|-----------|---------------------------------------------|
| Case caption           | Yes       | Must exactly match court caption             |
| Claimant full name     | Yes       | Alphabetic characters, allow spaces          |
| Contact info           | Yes       | Phone number, email format                     |
| Date fields            | Yes       | MM/DD/YYYY, clarify time zone if relevant     |
| Signature              | Yes       | Printed name + signature + date                |
| Claim category         | Yes       | Select listed category; no custom input       |

### Documentation Requirements

| Claim Type            | Required Documents                         | Alternatives / Notes                            |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Minor claimant        | Guardian authorization paperwork            | Submit estate or representative proof if applicable |
| Estate claimant       | Death certificate and estate letters         |                                                |
| Representative claim  | Power of attorney or court appointment       |                                                |
| General claim         | Proof of class membership                     | May waive if low payment threshold               |

## Certification and Release Checklist

- [ ] Include statement certifying truthfulness under penalty of perjury  
- [ ] Include waiver language per settlement agreement and court order  
- [ ] Add Cal. Civ. Code § 1542 waiver if state-specific release applies  
- [ ] Require signature and date for claimant or authorized representative  
- [ ] Include privacy acknowledgment and data use consent  

## Template Skeleton

```text
# Case Information  
- Case Caption: [Insert Case Caption]  
- Case Number: [Insert Case Number]  
- Court: [Insert Court Name]  
- Settlement Approval Order Date: [Insert Date]  

# Claimant Information  
- Full Name: [Insert Full Name]  
- Contact Information: [Phone, Email, Address]  
- Representative Name (if any): [Insert Name]  
- Relationship to Claimant: [Insert Relationship]  

# Class Action Eligibility Criteria  
- Class Definition Summary: [Insert Summary]  
- Relevant Dates and Periods: [Insert Dates]  

# Claim Categories and Payment Options  
- Category 1: [Description and Eligibility]  
- Category 2: [Description and Eligibility]  
- Other Categories: [As Applicable]  

# Documentation Checklist  
[List all required docs for categories]  

# Certification and Release Agreement  
I certify under penalty of perjury that the information provided is truthful and complete.  
I acknowledge and agree to the release terms as set forth in the settlement agreement.  
[If applicable] I waive rights under Cal. Civ. Code § 1542. [VERIFY]  

Signature: ___________________________ Date: ________________  

# Submission Instructions  
- Submit claims by: [Deadline Date and Time Zone]  
- Acceptable submission methods: [Mail, Email, Online Portal, etc.]  
- Postmark vs Received Date Rule: [Specify]  
- Settlement Administrator Contact: [Insert Contact Info]  

# For Settlement Administrator Use Only  
- Date Received: __________  
- Reviewer Initials: __________  
- Notes: ___________________  
```

## Guidelines

- Use plain language consistent with the settlement notice and court approval order  
- Do not guarantee claim payment; all payments are subject to fund availability and approval  
- Conform precisely to class eligibility and claim categories as defined in the settlement  
- Include accessible formats and options per ADA and Section 508 requirements  
- Provide for translation if required by settlement or jurisdiction  
- For minors or estate claims, require appropriate legal authority documentation  
- Respect privacy laws and limit collection of sensitive personal data unless court-ordered  
- Ensure submission methods accommodate E-SIGN compliance for electronic claims  
- Reminder: Claim submission deadlines must specify applicable time zones and postmark vs received date rules  
- Include the settlement administrator’s contact information prominently  
- If any state-specific release applies, specifically include Cal. Civ. Code § 1542 waiver language (mark as [VERIFY] if uncertain)  
- Use flat lists only; avoid nested bullet points per formatting standards  
- Maintain consistency with all official court and settlement documents  
- Do not provide legal advice or interpret settlement terms beyond stated guidance  

## Compliance Notes

- Federal Rules of Civil Procedure Rule 23 governs class action requirements  
- Settlement agreement and court approval order must drive all claim form content  
- Privacy policies must align with applicable privacy laws and E-SIGN regulations  
- Time zone and deadlines must be clear to avoid waiver of rights due to late submission  
- Make forms ADA accessible and provide reasonable accommodations for persons with disabilities  
- Translation requirements apply if class members include non-English speakers  
- Confirm all citations and waiver text accuracy; mark uncertain items with [VERIFY]

# End of Skill Content
